<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Crystal2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Crystal,</orth> adj. 1) made of crystal: <cit><quote>through c. walls each little mote will peep,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1251" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1251</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) bright: <cit><quote>the more fair and c. is the sky,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>comets, brandish your c. tresses in the sky,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy c. gate ope,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 81</bibl></cit>. Used of eyes: <bibl n="shak. ven 633" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 633</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 46.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 46, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 4, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 2, 101</bibl>. Of tears: <bibl n="shak. ven 491" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 491</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 491" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 491</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lc 286" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 286</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 171</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>